Shows network connection profiles

Get-NetConnectionProfile


Shows network adapters

Get-NetAdapter


Shows IP configuration

Get-NetIPConfiguration


Shows which protocols/services are bound to network adapters

Get-NetAdapterBinding


Classic command showing full network configuration

ipconfig /all


(Disables NetBIOS over TCP)

wmic nicconfig where TcpipNetbiosOptions=0 call SetTcpipNetbios 2


If you want to disable any protocol on the network – here is an example template:

Disable-NetAdapterBinding -Name "Ethernet" -ComponentID ms_implant


When you want to re-enable it:

Enable-NetAdapterBinding -Name "Ethernet" -ComponentID ms_implant


Disable "File and Printer Sharing for Microsoft Networks"

Disable-NetAdapterBinding -Name "Ethernet" -ComponentID ms_server




netsh int ipv4 show global


netsh int ipv6 show global


netsh interface ipv4 show interface "Ethernet"


netsh interface ipv6 show interface "Ethernet"


Command to disable ICMP Redirects in IPv4:

netsh interface ipv4 set global icmpredirects=disabled


Command to enable ICMP Redirects in IPv4:

netsh interface ipv4 set global icmpredirects=enabled


